# How you talk to AWS

Every interaction hits the **same control plane** — three doors in, all doing the same thing underneath.

## The three doors

- **Console** — web UI. For **learning** a service, one-off exploration.
- **CLI** — terminal commands. For **scripting**, automation glue, ad-hoc ops.
- **SDKs** (`boto3`) — from your code. For **app logic**, IaC, repeatable workflows.

## Underneath, all the same

All three send **signed HTTPS requests** to a regional **API endpoint**. Console = web app, CLI = thin wrapper, SDK = typed wrapper in your language.

## The habit

**Learn a service in the console**, then move to the **CLI or an SDK** once you want it **scripted and repeatable**.
